  canonicalUrl="/tree-surgeons/ai-whatsapp/"
  channelName="AI WhatsApp"
  tradeName="Tree Surgeon"
  tradeNamePlural="Tree Surgeons"
  tradeSlug="tree-surgeons"
  headline="AI WhatsApp for UK Tree Surgery Contractors"
  accentWord="Tree Surgery Contractors"
  subhead="A homeowner WhatsApps four photos of a large beech tree — fungal brackets emerging from the base, a longitudinal crack visible up the main stem, and two heavy limbs extending over the conservatory roof. Her message reads: 'This beech has been worrying me for two years. The crack is getting worse and I can see mushrooms at the bottom. Can you come and assess it urgently?' You are thirty feet up in an oak on the other side of the county, rigging a dying limb over a garage. Without AI WhatsApp, the message sits for five hours. With it, the homeowner gets an instant response, shares her postcode, and your lead summary — beech, fungal brackets, stem crack, over conservatory, urgent — is waiting with photos when you descend."
  scenario="It is 7:20am on a Saturday morning in January. Storm Jocelyn hit overnight. You are loading the truck at the yard — chipper on the trailer, ropes, slings, chainsaw kit — preparing for the first callout. Your phone has seventeen WhatsApp notifications queued up from the last two hours. Without AI WhatsApp, you scroll through them at the yard — photos of fallen trees, panicked messages, addresses scattered across the county — trying to mentally prioritise while loading equipment. Two hours of triage before you reach the first site. With AI WhatsApp, every homeowner received an instant response during the night and early morning. The AI captured: a mature willow uprooted into a river (ecologist involvement likely — medium priority), a leylandii row collapsed across a driveway (access blocked — high priority), a large horse chestnut split and resting on a cottage roof (structural damage — emergency), a pine snapped at mid-height hanging on a neighbouring tree (hung limb — dangerous), and thirteen moderate branch falls, fence damage, and hedge collapses. At 7:20am you open seventeen structured leads ranked by severity, dispatch your second crew to the cottage roof emergency, head to the hung pine yourself, and schedule the remaining work across the next three days."
  benefits={benefits}
  faqs={faqs}
  channelPageUrl="/construction-trades/ai-whatsapp/"
